        <h1 class="hero-title">Lion's Mane</h1>
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">The Focus Mushroom</p>
        <p>Lion's Mane (<em>Hericium erinaceus</em>) has been used in traditional Chinese and Japanese practices for centuries, valued for its ability to support focus and mental clarity. It was often consumed as a tea, including by monks during long periods of meditation.</p>
        <p>Today, it's one of the most widely studied functional mushrooms for cognitive performance, connecting centuries of use with modern research on brain health.</p>
